{"word":"ἀπεχθής","slug":"ἀπεχθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπεχθής</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔχθος'><el>ἔχθος</el></a>\n<p/><i>hateful, hostile</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀπεχθῶς ἔχειν τινι</el> <i>to be at enmity with</i> him, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/>"}]}